title: Amber Pyrops
description: Natural Amber Cast</br></br>Pyrops Candelaria</br></br>    An insect form not preserved within amber, but composed entirely of it. The process leading to such a formation is hypothetical, requiring an exceptional sequence of geological and biochemical events.</br></br>    Initially, a flowing resin trapped an insect, encasing it in a detailed negative mold. Over time, natural decomposition and mineral interactions dissolved the organic material, leaving a precise void within the hardened resin. Under specific conditions, new resin infiltrated the cavity, gradually replacing the lost structure. As the material polymerized and fossilized over millions of years, the result was a perfect positive castâ€”an insect sculpted from the very substance that once entombed it.
